record_data.record_plain_text:
Availability: Merck makes electric energy and capacity available under this tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below. Merck also makes available to any purchaser ancillary services, except as prohibited below:
PJM: Merck offers regulation and frequency response service for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
Third-Party Provider: Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third party supplier; and (3) sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers.
Applicability: This tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy, capacity and ancillary services by Merck at market-based rates.
Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Merck.
Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between Merck and the purchaser.
Compliance with Commission Regulations: Merck shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions that the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Merck's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Merck to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Merck's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any other orders of the Commission concerning Merck's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Merck does not have any limitation on its market-based rate authority, except as otherwise provided in this tariff. Merck has obtained waivers from Subparts B and C of Part 35, regarding the filing of tariffs, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; Part 41, regarding accounts, records, and memoranda; Part 101, regarding the uniform system of accounts; and Part 141, regarding statements and reports. Merck also has blanket approval under Part 34 of the Commission's regulations regarding future issuances of securities and assumptions of liabilities, subject to objection by an interested party. See Merck, Docket No. ER08-1299-000 (unpublished Letter Order) (____________, 2008).
Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
Effective Date: This tariff is effective September 23, 2008.
